---
/**
 * storage-engines · storage-engines-fundamentals · Figure 1 — the hero
 * "read/write/space" amplification triangle.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/storage-engines/storage-engines-fundamentals.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). It lives as an .astro component, NOT inline in
 * the MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses
 * kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size, stroke-width, …). In an .astro
 * file the SVG is plain HTML, so it renders byte-for-byte.
 */
---

<figure style="margin-top:1.6rem">
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 230"
        role="img"
        aria-label="The read/write/space triangle: every engine picks a corner; the page tours the curve from log to index to layout"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="320"
                y="26"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">THE ONE TENSION — you cannot make all three cheap at once</text
            >
            <!-- triangle -->
            <polygon
                points="320,52 116,196 524,196"
                fill="#fbfaf2"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.5"></polygon>
            <!-- vertices -->
            <circle cx="320" cy="52" r="5" fill="#7a1f12"></circle>
            <circle cx="116" cy="196" r="5" fill="#1f3a5a"></circle>
            <circle cx="524" cy="196" r="5" fill="#2f5d3a"></circle>
            <text
                x="320"
                y="44"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="13"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">READ amp</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="64" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >pages per lookup</text
            >
            <text
                x="96"
                y="214"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="13"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">WRITE amp</text
            >
            <text x="96" y="226" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >bytes rewritten</text
            >
            <text
                x="548"
                y="214"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="13"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">SPACE amp</text
            >
            <text x="548" y="226" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >disk vs data</text
            >
            <!-- where engines sit -->
            <g font-size="10">
                <rect x="232" y="96" width="112" height="22" rx="6" fill="#fff" stroke="#7a1f12"
                ></rect><text x="288" y="111" text-anchor="middle" fill="#7a1f12" font-weight="700"
                    >B-tree ↗ low read</text
                >
                <rect x="158" y="150" width="120" height="22" rx="6" fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"
                ></rect><text x="218" y="165" text-anchor="middle" fill="#1f3a5a" font-weight="700"
                    >LSM ↗ low write</text
                >
            </g>
            <text x="430" y="120" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >column store ↗</text
            >
            <text x="430" y="133" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >space via compression</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Memorise this triangle. Every level below is one engine, index, or layout choosing a corner
        — and paying in the other two.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
